&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'>&lt;b>&lt;span
style='font-size:16.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>CHRISTIAN
WORLD VIEW&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
basic reality in Christianity is interpersonalism. God is personal, and
everything else and everyone else derive from him by his creation. Interpersonalism
is the most complex reality there is. It stands in contrast to nature, law, and
ideas (metaphysics). Interpersonalism operates by love, nature by natural law,
law by authority, and metaphysics by form. &lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CONDITION vs. CAUSE</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/notion-in-a-nutshell/condition-vs-cause/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/notion-in-a-nutshell/condition-vs-cause/</guid><description>&lt;style>
