&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Good
and bad are figured relative to purpose. &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Out
of the nature of God comes the purpose of God.  Out of the purpose of God comes
the creation by God, of which we are a part, including people in relationship. There
is a fairly close fit between our nature and human morality, but the decisive
issue is God’s originating purpose.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>NATURAL DEPRAVITY</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/notion-in-a-nutshell/natural-depravity/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/notion-in-a-nutshell/natural-depravity/</guid><description>&lt;style>
