&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
threeness in oneness of God is comparable to the twoness in oneness of ideal
marriage—minus the physical distinctives. The Father, Son, and Spirit are
sufficiently distinct that the Son can &lt;u>pray&lt;/u> to the Father and the Father
can &lt;u>send&lt;/u> &lt;u>another&lt;/u> comforter (John &lt;b>14&lt;/b>:16).&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>TRUTH</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/notion-in-a-nutshell/truth/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/notion-in-a-nutshell/truth/</guid><description>&lt;style>
